==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
The first is a reduplicated and contracted form of the second (which occurs only as an alternate in certain tenses); probably akin to [[πέτομαι]] through the idea of alighting; 

===Pronunciation===
*πίπτω, πέτω / piptō  petō /  pip'-to, pet'-o

===Verb===
'''πίπτω'''

# to fall (literally of figuratively): - [[fail]], [[fall]] (down), [[light]] on.

